  "response": "Here are several effective ways to warm your hands before playing guitar:\n\n1. Physical methods:\n- Rub your hands together vigorously\n- Clap your hands\n- Do hand stretches and flexing exercises\n- Use hand warmers\n- Run your hands under warm (not hot) water\n- Put your hands in your armpits\n\n2. Additional preparation techniques:\n- Do gentle hand and finger exercises\n- Massage your hands and fingers\n- Use warm gloves before playing\n- Play in a warm room\n- Keep your guitar in a warm area before playing\n\n3. Long-term strategies:\n- Regular hand exercises\n- Maintain good overall circulation\n- Stay hydrated\n- Consider wearing fingerless gloves during practice\n\n4. Warm-up playing techniques:\n- Start with slow, gentle playing\n- Do scale exercises at a relaxed pace\n- Begin with simple chord progressions\n\nPro tips:\n- Avoid extreme heat\n- Don't use hot water (can damage skin)\n- Be gentle with cold hands to prevent strain\n\nRemember, consistently warm hands will help prevent stiffness and improve your playing comfort and technique.",
